{{Infobox person
| native_name        = 天曽利命
| children           = [[Hayato people]]
| father             = [[Hoderi]]<ref>''Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697'', translated from the original Chinese and Japanese by [[William George Aston]]. Book II, page 73. Tuttle Publishing. Tra edition (July 2005). First edition published 1972. {{ISBN|978-0-8048-3674-6}}</ref><ref>"According to the 'Kojiki', the great 8th century A.D. compilation of Japanese mythology, Konohana Sakuya-hime married a god who grew suspicious of her when she became pregnant shortly after their wedding. To prove her fidelity to her husband, she entered a benign [[Bedroom|bower]] and miraculously gave birth to a son, unscathed by the surrounding flames. The fire ceremony at Fuji-Yyoshida recalls this story as a means of protecting the town from fire and promoting easy childbirth among women."</ref>
}}

'''Tensori no Mikoto''' (天曽利命) is considered the {{Interlanguage link|Oyagami}} of the {{Ill|Hayato people|en}}<ref name="A109 天曽利命">{{Cite web|title=A109 天曽利命|url=https://www.his-trip.info/keizu/entry46.html|access-date=2023-12-14|website=www.his-trip.info|language=ja}}</ref><ref name="sakura.ne.jp">{{Cite web|date=2016-03-19|title=�v�Ď��l|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319134404/http://ek1010.sakura.ne.jp/1234-7-41.html|access-date=2024-01-06|website=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref name="ﾑｰﾀﾞﾝ">{{Cite web|title=【ﾑｰﾀﾞﾝ】李氏朝鮮VS琉球王国7【ﾕﾀ】|url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:27J1abZ5nb0J:mimizun.com/log/2ch/korea/1347841276/|access-date=2024-01-06|website=webcache.googleusercontent.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EL0nAAAAYAAJ&newbks=0&printsec=frontcover&dq=%22%E5%A4%A9%E6%9B%BD%E5%88%A9%E5%91%BD%22&q=%22%E5%A4%A9%E6%9B%BD%E5%88%A9%E5%91%BD%22&hl=en|title=古代氏族系譜集成|last=Hōga|first=Toshio|last2=宝賀寿男|date=1986|publisher=古代氏族研究会|language=zh-TW}}</ref><ref>[https://ndlsearch.ndl.go.jp/books/R100000002-I000002274014 古代豪族系図集覧]</ref>.

== Explanation ==
He is said to be the older brother of {{Interlanguage link|Ahiratsu-hime|4=en}} (吾平津媛), the first wife of [[Emperor Jimmu]]. <ref name="A109 天曽利命">{{Cite web|title=A109 天曽利命|url=https://www.his-trip.info/keizu/entry46.html|access-date=2023-12-14|website=www.his-trip.info|language=ja}}</ref>

Tensori no Mikoto is sometimes identified with Agatanushi Obashi (吾田君小橋) <ref name="sakura.ne.jp">{{Cite web|date=2016-03-19|title=�v�Ď��l|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319134404/http://ek1010.sakura.ne.jp/1234-7-41.html|access-date=2024-01-06|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> .

It is possible that Tensori no Mikoto is {{Interlanguage link|Hosuseri|4=en}}'s son <ref name="ﾑｰﾀﾞﾝ">{{Cite web|title=【ﾑｰﾀﾞﾝ】李氏朝鮮VS琉球王国7【ﾕﾀ】|url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:27J1abZ5nb0J:mimizun.com/log/2ch/korea/1347841276/|access-date=2024-01-06|website=webcache.googleusercontent.com}}</ref> .

